sequenceDiagram
    participant "System Under Monitoring (e.g., API Gateway)" as SystemUnderMonitoringegAPIGateway
    participant "Amazon CloudWatch" as AmazonCloudWatch
    participant "Amazon SNS" as AmazonSNS
    participant "On-Call Engineer Endpoint" as OnCallEngineerEndpoint

    activate AmazonCloudWatch
    SystemUnderMonitoringegAPIGateway->>AmazonCloudWatch: 1. Emit Performance Metric Data Point
    AmazonCloudWatch->>AmazonCloudWatch: 2. Evaluate 'API_Performance_Degraded_Latency' Alarm
    AmazonCloudWatch-->>AmazonCloudWatch: Evaluation Result: Threshold Breached
    AmazonCloudWatch->>AmazonCloudWatch: 3. Threshold Breached: Transition State from 'OK' to 'ALARM'
    activate AmazonSNS
    AmazonCloudWatch->>AmazonSNS: 4. Invoke Alarm Action: Publish Notification
    AmazonSNS->>AmazonSNS: 5. Fan-out Message to All Topic Subscribers
    AmazonSNS->>OnCallEngineerEndpoint: 6. Deliver Alert Notification via Subscriber Protocol

    note over AmazonCloudWatch: Alarm thresholds are not arbitrary; they are derived directly from the Non-Functional Requirement...
    note over AmazonSNS: A DLQ (SQS Queue) should be configured on the SNS subscription to capture failed deliveries. This...

    deactivate AmazonSNS
    deactivate AmazonCloudWatch
